cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.SD, cs.LG, cs.AI. 

This paper involves the use of computer vision and natural language processing techniques to learn from untranscribed speech and images, which suggests that it could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories. The most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language) since the paper deals with language acquisition and speech recognition. The use of visual cues and image-to-words mapping also suggests that it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.SD (Sound) sub-categories. The paper also involves the use of neural networks, which could place it in cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories.
